FBIS3-57560 "drsov018_d_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-018 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Jan 1994 Regional Affairs Ingushetia Seeks To Retain Federation Status MK2601143094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 26 Jan 94 p 2 MK2601143094 Moscow SEGODNYA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report in the "Provincial Chronicle" column] [Text] Nazran -- Speaking on local TV, Murat Keligov, adviser to the Ingushetia president, stated that the republic's future constitution "must record an unequivocal provision" that it is part of the Russian Federation. The future fundamental law should reflect Ingushetia's sovereignty and its struggle, "exclusively by political means," to ensure the return of the territory of Prigorodnyy Rayon, which now belongs to North Ossetia.
